.TH "scsi_mode_select" 9 "scsi_mode_select" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
scsi_mode_select \- issue a mode select
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" scsi_mode_select
.BI "(struct scsi_device *sdev "  ","
.BI "int pf "  ","
.BI "int sp "  ","
.BI "int modepage "  ","
.BI "unsigned char *buffer "  ","
.BI "int len "  ","
.BI "int timeout "  ","
.BI "int retries "  ","
.BI "struct scsi_mode_data *data "  ","
.BI "struct scsi_sense_hdr *sshdr "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "sdev" 12
SCSI device to be queried
.IP "pf" 12
Page format bit (1 == standard, 0 == vendor specific)
.IP "sp" 12
Save page bit (0 == don't save, 1 == save)
.IP "modepage" 12
mode page being requested
.IP "buffer" 12
request buffer (may not be smaller than eight bytes)
.IP "len" 12
length of request buffer.
.IP "timeout" 12
command timeout
.IP "retries" 12
number of retries before failing
.IP "data" 12
returns a structure abstracting the mode header data
.IP "sshdr" 12
place to put sense data (or NULL if no sense to be collected).
must be SCSI_SENSE_BUFFERSIZE big.

Returns zero if successful; negative error number or scsi
status on error
